% haste mūrdhnyupavīte vā \T32
yaśca bhuñjīta bhasmāṅgī rudrairbhuktanna saṃśayaḥ|| 12.88||
% yaśca bhūṃjīta tadbhuktaṃ rudro bhuṃkte svayaṃ prabhuḥ| \T32
rudrākṣadhāraṇāt tasmānnityameva praśasyate|
% rudrākṣadhāraṇaṃ tasmāt  \T32
parātmānugrahārthaṃ hi brāhmaṇasya viśeṣataḥ|| 12.89||
% parātmānugrahārthāya \T32
yatimātropakaraṇaṃ datvālpamapi bhaktitaḥ|
varṣalakṣaṃ mahābhogaiḥ śivaloke mahīyate|| 12.90||
kuryādāvasathaṃ saumyaṃ suguptaṃ śivayoginām|
śivālayakṛte yāvat tāvat puṇyaṃ samaṃ bhavet|| 12.91||
% śivālayakṛteryāvat \T32
yathā śivastathā yogī yathā yogī tathā śivaḥ|
tena yogīndrapātreṣu dānamapyalpamakṣayam|| 12.92||
% dānamaṇvapi cākṣayam| \T32
yadyadasyopayujyeta taddeyan tat prayatnataḥ|
% taddeyaṃ tasya bhaktitaḥ| \T32
upayogapradānābhyāṃ śreyastenobhayorapi|| 12.93||
% upayogapradānena praśastaṃ lokamāpnuyāt| \T32
%% p.175
vyākhyāne śivadharmasya kṛtvā maṇḍalakaṃ mahat|
% kṛtvā maṇḍapamuttamam| \T32
śobhitaṃ puṣpapatrādyaiḥ śivadharmāsanaṃ mahat|| 12.94||
% śobhitaṃ mṛdugandhādyaiḥ nyasettatrāsanaṃ śubham| \T32
purastasya guroḥ sthāpya pūjayedubhayantataḥ|
% pustakaṃ tadguroḥ sthāpya pūjayedubhayaṃ tataḥ| \T32
śivadharmapravaktāram ācāryaṃ pūjayet sadā|| 12.95||
% ācāryaṃ pūjayet tataḥ| \T32
śivavacchivadharmaśca tulyametaddvayantataḥ|
% śivaśca śivadharmaśca tulyameva na saṃśayaḥ| \T32
ya evaṃ nayāyato bhaktaḥ śivadharmaṃ śṛṇoti ca|| 12.96||
% ya evaṃ nyāyato bhaktyā \T32
āyurvidyāṃ yaśaḥ saukhyaṃ labdhvānte sa śivaṃ vrajet| <-- referring to the story of Atri/Kṛṣṇātreya receiving the Āyurveda
% labdhvānte tu śivaṃ vrajet| \T32
ityeṣa vaḥ samākhyātaḥ śivadharmaḥ sanātanaḥ|| 12.97||
sarveṣāṃ śivabhaktānām ayaṃ vācyo vijānatā|
śivāśrameṣu yo bhaktaḥ śivadharmaṃ prakīrtayet|| 12.98||
% śivāśremeṣu yo bhaktyā śivadharmaṃ pravartayet| \T32
śṛṇuyādvāpi labhate tatroktamakhilaṃ phalam|
% śṛṇuyācca bhavettasya śāstroktamakhilaṃ phalam| \T32
śrutvaivamakhilaṃ dharmam ākhyātaṃ brahmasūnunā|| 12.99||
candrātreyasagotrāya śivabhaktāya sāravat|
sārātsāraṃ samuddhṛtya candrātreyeṇa dhīmatā|| 12.100||
uktañca dvādaśādhyāyaṃ dharmaśāstraṃ śivātmakam|
% uktañca dvādaśakādhyāyaṃ \T32
yāvadasyopadeśena śivadharmaṃ samācaret|| 12.101||
tāvattsyāpi tatpuṇuam upadeśanna saṃśayaḥ|
% uapadeṣṭurnasaṃśayaḥ| \T32
upadeśaṃ vinā yasmāddharmojñātuṃ na śakyate|| 12.102||
%% p.176
%% This page records no verses; instead, it records only the commentary of the editor Naraharinath.
%% p.177
na cākartumavijñāya tasmāttulyaṃ phalaṃ tayoḥ|
% na ca kartumavijñānāt tasmāttulyaṃ tayoḥ phalam| \T32
upadeṣṭānumantā ca kartā kārayitā ca yaḥ|| 12.103||
kṛtānupālakaścaiva pañca tulyaphalāḥ smṛtāḥ|
karturapyadhikaṃ puṇyaṃ tatkṛtaṃ yo.anupālayet|| 12.104||
% tatkṛtaṃ yastu pālayet| \T32
yasmādāyatanaṃ kṣipraṃ nāśaṅgacchatyapālitam|
% nāśaṃ gacchedapālitam| \T32
bhūmiratnāśvanāgānāṃ gohiraṇyādivāsasām|| 12.105||
% būmiratnāśca nāgānāṃ  \T32
bhavet pūrvopari sthānaṃ dānāccheyo.anupālanam|
% bhavetpūrvopasṛṣṭhānāṃ dānācchreyonupālanam| \T32
dāturabhyādhikaṃ puṇyaṃ dattaṃ yaścānupālayet|| 12.106||
% dāturapyadhikaṃ puṇyaṃ taddattaṃ yo.anupālayet| \T32
apālitantu tadyasmācchhīghrameva praṇaśyati|
% tatpālitaṃ tu tadyatnāt śīghrameva praṇaśyate| \T32
tasmādupadiśeddharmaṃ svayaṃ vāpi samācaret|| 12.107||
kārayeddānam ityeva kṛtamanyaiśca pālayet|
% kārayedanumanyaita kṛtamanyaiśca pālayet| \T32
%% pañcāṣṭaka
  pāśupataṃ   rudrakoṭir avimuktaṃ mahālayaḥ|| 12.108|| % vastrāpadaṃ mahākoṭir  avimukta  mahālayam| \T32
  gokarṇo  bhadrakarṇaś ca suvarṇokṣo .atha dīptimān| % gokarṇaṃ bhadrakarṇaṃ ca suvarṇākṣaṃ ca   dīptimat| \T32
  sthāṇvīśvaraś ca vikhyātaṃs triṣu lokeṣu viśrutam|| 12.109|| % sthāṇvīśvaraṃ ca vikhyātaṃ  triṣu lokeṣu viśrutam| \T32
  sthānam aṣṭakam idaṃ jñeyaṃ rudrakṣetraṃ mahodayam| % sthānāṣṭakam    idaṃ jñeyaṃ rudrakṣetra  mahodayam| \T32
  pāśupatādisthāṇvantaṃ rudrasāyujyakāraṇam|| 12.110|| % vastrāpadādisthāṇvantaṃ rudrasāyujyamāpnuyāt| \T32
  chagaraṇḍo  duraṇḍaś ca mākoṭaṃ maṇḍaleśvaram| % chagalaṇḍaṃ ciraṇḍaṃ ca mākoṭaṃ maṇḍaleśvaram| \T32
kālañjaraṃ śaṅkukarṇaṃ sthaleśvaraḥ sthūleśvaraḥ|| 12.111|| %                      sthūleśvaraṃ sthaleśvaram| \T32
pavitrāṣṭakam ity etan mahāpuṇyābhivardhanam|
mṛtāḥ prayānti tatraiva śivasya paramaṃ padam|| 12.112|| % śivākhyaṃ paramaṃ padam| \T32
devaghaṭṭaṃ kurukṣetraṃ nakhalaṃ kanakhalaṃ tathā| % gayā caiva kurukṣetraṃ nākhalaṃ nakhalaṃ tathā| \T32
%% p.178
vimaleśvaro.aṭṭahāsaṃ mahendraṃ bhīmamaṣṭakam|| 12.113|| % vimalaṃ cāṭṭahāsaṃ ca \T32
etad guhyāṣṭakaṃ nāma sarvapāpavimocanam| % etad guhyāṣṭakaṃ nāthaṃ \T32
gatvā tu puruṣaḥ śrīmān prāpnoti śivamandiram|| 12.114||
śrīparvataṃ hariścandraṃ jalpam āmrātakeśvaram| % jalpamāmrādikeśvaram| \T32
madhyamañ ca mahākālaṃ kedāraṃ bhairavan tathā|| 12.115||
etad guhyātiguhyañca aṣṭakaṃ parikīrtitam| % aṣṭakaṃ samudāhṛtam| \T32
santarpya tu pitṝn sarvān śivaṃ yānti paraṃ padam|| 12.116|| % santarpya ca pitṝn sarvān śivaṃ śāntaṃ padaṃ vrajet| \T32
āmreśvaraṃ prabhārañ ca naimiṣaṃ puṣkarāntathā| % amareśaṃ prabhāsaṃ ca naimiśaṃ puṣkaraṃ tathā| \T32
āṣāḍhiṃ diṇḍimuṇḍiñca bhārabhūtiṃ bhavāntakam|| 12.117|| % āṣāḍhī daṇḍi muṇḍi ca bhārabhūś ca lākulam| \T32
nakulīśvaro.atha vikhyātas tathā pratyātmiko mahān| % lakulīśvaraṃ ca vikhyātaṃ tathā pratyātmako mahān| \T32
%% p.179
pratyātmikāṣṭakṣetraṃ rudrasya hitakāmyayā|| 12.118|| % pratyātmikāṣṭakamidaṃ kṣetraṃ rudrasya kīrtitam| \T32
tatra yānti mṛtāḥ sarve rudrasya paramaṃ padam| % pañcāṣṭakamidaṃ jñeyaṃ śivakṣetrasya lakṣaṇam| \T32
%% In T32 this pañcāṣṭaka section (verse 108cd - 119ab) occurs
%% in between verse 50cd to 51ab of this edition.
dānānyāvasathaṃ kūpam udyānandevatālayam|| 12.119||
tīrthevetāni yaḥ kuryāt so.akṣayaṃ phalamāpnuyāt| % tīrtheṣveteṣu \T32
kṣamā spṛhā dayā satyaṃ dānaṃ śīlantapaḥ śrutam|| 12.120||
%% p.180
etadaṣṭāṅgamuddiṣṭaṃ paraṃ pātrasya lakṣaṇam|
%% Verses 119ab - 121ab are repetition of verses 51ab - 52cd,
%% of this edition, with minor veriation. These verses are missing in T32.
iti pañcaprakāro.ayaṃ śivadharmaḥ prakīrtitaḥ|| 12.121||
dharmārthakāmamokṣārthaṃ sarvabhūtānukampayā|
% kapālamālindeveśa mahākāla namo.astu te| \T32
% candrārdhamūrdhan bhūteśa carmavāsaḥ sadāpriya| \T32
% gajacarmarata svāmin caṇḍanātha namo.astu te| \T32
% triśūlapāṇe deveśa triṇetra tridaśeśvara| \T32
% trimūrte ca mahāyogin tripurāntaka te namaḥ| \T32
% sarveśa he sarvagata sarvavitsarvatomukha| \T32
% sarvatrāvasthito.ananta sarvavyāpinnamo.astu te| \T32
% sthūlasūkṣmavibhā  . . vyāptaṃ yena carācaram| \T32
% anantānādikāvyaktavyaktāvyaktāya te namaḥ| \T32
% śrīkaṇṭhaṃ sarpakaṇṭhaṃ ca nīlakaṇṭhaṃ namāmyaham| \T32
% vidyāmayī tanuryasya vidyādhīnaṃ ca tat sthitam| \T32
% skalaṃ niṣkalaṃ caiva kalāhīna namo.astu te| \T32
% yogādhipo yogagamyo yogātmā yogasambhavaḥ| \T32
% mahāyogadharo yaśca yogeśvara namo.astu te| \T32
% srvaṃ tejomayaṃ dehaṃ tejasāmapi tejasam| \T32
% tejonidhiśca yaścedaṃ tejotīta namo.astu te| \T32
% omityekākṣaraṃ yattu prakhyātaṃ bhuvanatraye| \T32
% tasyāpyarthapayorastu sadāśivanamo.astu te| \T32
% ardhamātraparārdhaṃ yat tasyārdhasya tu yo.adhipaḥ| \T32
% parāparaṃ paraṃ śāntaṃ śāntyātīta namo.astu te| \T32
% akārokārayorūrdhvaṃ makāro vindureva ca| \T32
% nirvāṇaparamātīta tadatīta namo.astu te| \T32
% vālāgraśatabhāgasya śatadhā kalpitaṃ ca yat| \T32
% anaupamyamanāmaṃ ca śiva śānta namo.astu te| \T32
% anantānādimavyaktaṃ dehasthaṃ dehavarjitam| \T32
% hṛdisthaṃ sarvabhūteṣu vyomasthaṃ yannamo.astu te| \T32
% agrāhyamindriyairvāyat sarvavastuvivarjitam| \T32
% svadeśe gūḍhamānantaguhāvāsa namo.astu te| \T32
% guhātītaśca gūḍhātmā guhyānāṃ guhyagocara| \T32
% śubhāvāsaśca yo nityaṃ gūḍhārthaṃ ca namo.astu te| \T32
% mahādeva mahābodha mahāmāya mahābala| \T32
% mahājñāna parātīta jñānaguhya namo.astu te| \T32
% īśānamīśvaraṃ brahma sadāśivamajaṃ param| \T32
% nirdvandvaṃ nirmalaṃ sākṣāt yaṃ maheśa namo.astu te| \T32
% ekākṣaraṃ carbhedaṃ caturmaṃtrairalaṃkṛtam| \T32
% catuṣkalaṃ kalātītaṃ bindvatīta namo.astu te| \T32
% iti stavena divyena yaḥ stauti parameśvaram| \T32
% sa muktaḥ sarvapāpebhyaḥ śivasāyujyamāpnuyāt| \T32
%% Above verses are missing in the printed edition, from Nepal.
sarvastaratu durgāṇi sarve bhadrāṇi paśyatu|| 122||
% sarvastaratu durgāṇi sarvo bhadrāṇi paśyatu| \T32
sarvaḥ sugatimāpnotu srvasya ca bhavecchivaḥ|
% sarvaḥ sugatimāpnotu sarvasya tu bhavecchivam| \T32
oṃ mahādevāya candramūrtaye namaḥ||
oṃ īśānāya sūryamūrtaye namaḥ||
oṃ ugrāya vāyumūtaye namaḥ||
oṃ rudrāyā.agnimūtaye namaḥ||
oṃ bhavāya jalamūrtaye namaḥ||
oṃ śarvāya kṣitimūrtaye namaḥ||
oṃ paśupataye yajamānamūrtaye namaḥ||
oṃ bhīmā.a.akāśamūrtaye namaḥ||
mūrtyayoṣṭau śivasyetāḥ pūrvādikramayogataḥ|
āgneyāntāḥ prayojyāḥ syustābhyaḥ śivāṅgapūjanam|| 123||

%% In MS Add 1695, from Cambridge University, the passage on the places of the pañcāṣṭaka occurs in the
%% same sequence as it occurs in the printed edition.
%% And the large number of verses, which are missing in the printed edition,
%% are also missing in this MS.
%% Moreover, the concluding portion of this MS is very similar to
%% the concluding portion of the printed edition.

\Colo
iti śivadharmaśāstre nandikeśvaraprokte śivabhaktyādyaśākhopaśākhā dvādaśo.adhyāyaḥ||
% iti śivadharmaśāstre nandikeśvaraprokte śivadharmaśāstre
% dvādaśo.adhyāyaḥ śivadharme pūrvaṃ saṃpūrṇam| \T32





